    34   * <p>This implements the modern discovery strategy, which uses only service loading in order to discover plugins.
    35   * Specifically, a plugin appears in the scan result if all the following conditions are true:
    36   * <ul>
    37   *     <li>The class and direct dependencies can be loaded</li>
    38   *     <li>The class is concrete</li>
    39   *     <li>The class is public</li>
    40   *     <li>The class has a no-args constructor</li>
    41   *     <li>The no-args constructor is public</li>
    42   *     <li>Static initialization of the class completes without throwing an exception</li>
    43   *     <li>The no-args constructor completes without throwing an exception</li>
    44   *     <li>The class is a subclass of {@link SinkConnector}, {@link SourceConnector}, {@link Converter},
    45   *         {@link HeaderConverter}, {@link Transformation}, {@link Predicate}, {@link ConfigProvider},
    46   *         {@link ConnectRestExtension}, or {@link ConnectorClientConfigOverridePolicy}
    47   *     </li>
    48   *     <li>The class has a {@link ServiceLoader} compatible manifest file or module declaration</li>
    49   * </ul>
    50   * <p>Note: This scanner can only find plugins with corresponding {@link ServiceLoader} manifests, which are
    51   * not required to be packaged with plugins. This has the effect that some plugins discoverable by the
    52   * {@link ReflectionScanner} may not be visible with this implementation.
    53   */
    54  public class ServiceLoaderScanner extends PluginScanner {
